This paper discusses a new method for improving the convergence of adaptive learning rate methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning. The paper focuses on the Adam optimizer and proposes a new method called AdaShift. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
